title.narrative: Targeted members of Communities have enhanced capacity to effectively prevent and respond to practices and behaviors harmful tochildren (inUNICEF targeted districts)

description.narrative: With UNICEF support, efforts to prevent violence against children, in line with the NPA-VAWC and its Integrated Communication and Outreach Strategy, were coordinated and implemented in five regions in 2021, enhancing the role of children, adolescents, caregivers and communities in building a protective environment for children. Across these regions, an additional 2,389 religious and traditional leaders and influential elders (cumulative 4,739) were trained on violence prevention and are taking action in communities to raise awareness about violence, 38,602 parents and caregivers (cumulative 92,068) have benefitted from positive parenting programmes, and 10,073 schools (cumulative 19,292) were reached with violence prevention interventions. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:22/12/2021
